This file ensures the empty_pack/ directory exists in git.

The `pack_discovery::pack_empty_directory_warns` test in
`tests/test_cli_hardening.rs` runs `cjcl pack empty_pack/ --dry-run` and
asserts the CLI emits a "no packable files found" warning. For that to
work, the directory itself must exist — git doesn't track empty
directories, so this `.gitkeep` marker is the standard idiom.

Do not add other files to this directory; it's deliberately empty.
